eeanga-Yamahtta Taylor calls for the defunding of police and the refunding of communities; Keisha Blain demonstrates why the battle against racism must be global; and Adam Tooze reveals that COVID-19 hit hardest where inequality was already greatest and welfare states weakest. Yarimar Bonilla, Xiaowei Wang, Simon Balto, Marcia Chatelain, Gautam Bhan, Ananya Roy, and others offer insights from the factory farms of China to the elite resorts of France, the meatpacking plants of the Midwest to the overcrowded hospitals of India.The definitive guide to these ongoing catastrophes, The Long Year shows that only by exposing the roots and ramifications of 2020 can another such breakdown be prevented. It is made possible through institutional partnerships with Public Books and the Social Science Research Council.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aCOVID-19 (Disease)xSocial aspects. 0aEconomic developmenty21st century. 0aEconomic development-History-21st century. 0aEqualityxSocial aspects. 0aEquality-Social aspects. 0aPolicexPolitical aspects. 0aRacial justice. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / American Government / General.2bisacsh  aBig Lie.  aBlack Lives Matter.  aCOVID-19.  aCOVID.  aJanuary 6.  aTrump.  acapitalism.  ademocracy.  aelection.  ainequality.  ainjustice.  apandemic.  apolice violence.  aprotest.  asocial unrest.1 aAfsahi, Afsoun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAl Dahdah, Marine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAmir, Sulfikar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnderson, Warwick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaiocchi, Gianpaolo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBalto, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https